      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'm looking at a vendor contract for our supply chain. There's a clause regarding \"force majeure\" that mentions \"unforeseeable events beyond the reasonable control of the parties.\" If a regional power grid failure occurs due to an unexpected storm, would that typically qualify as a force majeure event under standard commercial terms?",
