      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'm not really sure I follow the analogy. Can you just stick to the legal aspects? Specifically, if the contract doesn't explicitly list \"power outages\" or \"grid failures\" in the clause, but only uses general language like \"acts of God,\" does the storm/outage scenario still hold up as a valid trigger?",
